scene"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"collapsed":false,"originalKey":"74c60677-f3d1-4243-8a88-b97e9a387e4d","requestMsgId":"74c60677-f3d1-4243-8a88-b97e9a387e4d","customOutput":null,"executionStartTime":1727914393400,"executionStopTime":1727914396634,"outputsInitialized":true,"language":"python","serverExecutionDuration":2684.2039106414,"isAgentGenerated":false},"source":["image_height, image_width = 1024, 1024\n","\n","camera_distance = 0.5\n","a1 = np.pi\n","a2 = 1\n","a3 = 0\n","offset = np.array([0, 0.1, 0])\n","\n","# Let's say we have only v and vi\n","v, vt, _, vi, vti, _ = igl.read_obj(\"bunny.obj\")\n","v = th.tensor(v, dtype=th.float32)[None, ...].cuda()\n","vi = th.tensor(vi, dtype=th.int32).cuda()\n","vt = th.tensor(vt, dtype=th.float32).cuda()\n","vti = th.tensor(vti, dtype=th.int32).cuda()\n","\n","def rodrigues(x):\n","    x, _ = cv2.Rodrigues(np.asarray(x, dtype=np.float64))\n","    return np.float64(x)\n","\n","# camera extrinsics\n","t = np.array([0, 0, camera_distance], dtype=np.float64)\n","R = np.matmul(np.matmul(rodrigues([a1, 0, 0]), rodrigues([0, a2, 0])), rodrigues([0, 0, a3]))\n","cam_pos = th.as_tensor((R.transpose(-1, -2) \u0040 -t[..., None])[..., 0] + offset, dtype=th.float32).cuda()[None]\n","cam_rot = th.as_tensor(R, dtype=th.float32).cuda()[None]\n","\n","# camera intrinsics\n","focal = th.as_tensor([[2 * image_width, 0.0], [0.0, 2 * image_height]], dtype=th.float32).cuda()[None]\n","princpt = th.as_tensor(\n","    [image_width \/ 2, image_height \/ 2],\n","    dtype=th.float32,\n",").cuda()[None]"],"execution_count":2,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"originalKey":"f3c189fc-05e4-4e00-9e4a-07ab2e1b8fc0","showInput":false,"customInput":null,"language":"markdown"},"source":["## Compute mesh normals"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"originalKey":"a5eadb8d-0fa1-4dbb-b795-10d202f96f81","showInput":true,"customInput":null,"language":"python","executionStartTime":1727914396639,"executionStopTime":1727914397761,"serverExecutionDuration":547.26922139525,"collapsed":false,"requestMsgId":"a5eadb8d-0fa1-4dbb-b795-10d202f96f81","outputsInitialized":true},"source":["def face_normals(\n","    v: th.Tensor, vi: th.Tensor, normalize: bool = True, eps: float = 1e-8\n","):\n","    B = v.shape[0]\n","    NF = vi.shape[0]\n","    p = th.index_select(\n","        v,\n","        dim=1,\n","        index=vi.view(\n","            -1,\n","        ),\n","    ).view(B, NF, 3, 3)\n","    fn = th.linalg.cross(p[:, :, 0] - p[:, :, 2], p[:, :, 1] - p[:, :, 0], dim=-1)\n","    if normalize:\n","        fn = thf.normalize(fn, dim=-1, eps=eps)\n","    return fn\n","\n","\n","def face_attribute_to_vert(v: th.Tensor, vi: th.Tensor, attr: th.Tensor) -> th.Tensor:\n","    attr = (\n","        attr[:, :, None]\n","        .expand(-1, -1, 3, -1)\n","        .reshape(attr.shape[0], -1, attr.shape[-1])\n","    )\n","    vi_flat = vi.view(vi.shape[0], -1).expand(v.shape[0], -1)\n","    vattr = th.zeros(v.shape[:-1], dtype=v.dtype, device=v.device)\n","\n","    vattr = th.stack(\n","        [vattr.scatter_add(1, vi_flat, attr[..., i]) for i in range(attr.shape[-1])],\n","        dim=-1,\n","    )\n","    return vattr\n","\n","\n","def vert_normals(\n","    v: th.Tensor, vi: th.Tensor, normalize: bool = True, eps: float = 1e-8\n","):\n","    assert vi.dtype == th.int64\n","    # NOTE: we do not need to normalize face normals prior to re-sampling\n","    fn = face_normals(v, vi, normalize=False)\n","    vn = face_attribute_to_vert(v, vi[np.newaxis], fn)\n","    if normalize:\n","        vn = thf.normalize(vn, dim=-1, eps=eps)\n","    return vn\n","\n","\n","# compute screen-space normals\n","av3d = (cam_rot[:, None] \u0040 (v - cam_pos[:, None])[..., None])[..., 0]\n","normals = -vert_normals(av3d, vi.long())"],"execution_count":3,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"originalKey":"3928ba3b-33fe-4a48-835f-4b6453f97979","showInput":false,"customInput":null,"language":"markdown","outputsInitialized":false,"isAgentGenerated":false},"source":["## Rendering"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"originalKey":"2175b2c8-e043-409a-8d5f-94e256ddeda0","showInput":true,"customInput":null,"collapsed":false,"requestMsgId":"2175b2c8-e043-409a-8d5f-94e256ddeda0","customOutput":null,"executionStartTime":1727914397767,"executionStopTime":1727914398312,"outputsInitialized":true,"language":"python","serverExecutionDuration":39.767951704562,"isAgentGenerated":false},"source":["# convert verteices positions to image space\n","v_pix = drtk.transform(v, cam_pos, cam_rot, focal, princpt)\n","\n","# rasterize. This operation is not differentiable. You would need to use edge_grad_estimator\n","index_img = drtk.rasterize(v_pix, vi, image_height, image_width)\n","\n","# compute mesh mask. We add an additional dimention, to make it easily comatible with other BxCxHxW tensors\n","mask = (index_img != -1)[:, None]\n","\n","# compute differentiable depth and barycentric coordinates\n","depth_img, bary_img = drtk.render(v_pix, vi, index_img)\n","\n","# interpolate normals in image space\n","vn_img = drtk.interpolate(normals, vi, index_img, bary_img)\n","\n","# interpolate uv coordinates in image space. Notice that vti is used and not vi\n","vt_img = drtk.interpolate(vt.expand(v.shape[0], -1, -1), vti, index_img, bary_img)"],"execution_count":4,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"originalKey":"ba72b569-f45d-465f-bb76-975db39e524c","showInput":false,"customInput":null,"language":"markdown","outputsInitialized":false,"isAgentGenerated":false},"source":["##
